<TITLE> Kaneria given warning by ICC for swearing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, July 22 (bdnews24.com/Reuters)  Pakistan leg spinner Danish Kaneria was found guilty and given a warning for uttering an expletive in the third Test against Sri Lanka, the International Cricket Council (ICC) said on Wednesday. Kaneria was heard using obscene language by two on-field umpires after he had taken the wicket of Angelo Mathews on the second day of the final Test on Tuesday. The incident was also picked up by a stump microphone. "Danish knows what he said was unacceptable but in coming to my decision I took into account the fact that he apologised both immediately after the incident and in the hearing," match referee Alan Hurst said in a statement. "I am also content that the action was not directed at the batsman or any other individual and that the action was one more of frustration than anger." Sri Lanka have already won the series after taking an unassailable 2-0 
